title: For Sale:  Browning Electronic Air Rifle
postcontent:
This is from my Browning collection, a very rare Browning Electronic Air Rifle, made in Belgium.  It runs on a 7.2V rechargable battery that is self contained inside the buttstock and it drives an electric motor which cocks the spring mechanism with a push of a button, which is located on the trigger guard just behind the trigger.  There is an 'on-off' main switch located on the pistol grip area of the stock which turns the main power on.  Once the battery is fully charged, it can run approx. 300 shots before recharging again.  Another unique feature is the loading port, which is located on top of the fixed barrel, it flips open and there is a generous loading area where you can place a pellet into it, then just close the port cover.  The trigger is electronic, with no creep, no over travel, and has an automatic safety as well.
This was only imported into US by Browning for a very short time during the 80's and I had it kept in the back of the safe, only test fired a few dozen times.
It has a beautiful walnut stock with a nice rubber buttplate and very fine micro-meter, interchagable front sights and adjustable rear sight.  This is complete with box, extra front sight inserts, etc. in like new condition, with the factory AC charger.
Besides being a highly collectible Browning, it is also a very fun shooting, nicely build air rifle that is unique and classy at the same time.
